@node "A Propos" "About"
@next "Introduction"
@prev "Main"
This program will help you to make Pictures Index with ImageFX.

It is based on an ARexx script made by my brother Olivier. This script  was very
good but not easy to use, so i decided to write this @{"MUI" link "MUI" 0}  application which send
Arexx commands to ImageFX.

This Program is @{bg shine}GIFTWARE@{bg back}. If you use it, send me one (or more) floppy disk with
pictures or whatever you want (money welcome too). You can also send me a postal
card or just a letter, no problem. But you can't sell this program, or make
money with it without my agreement. This Archive must also remains as it was
originally spread by me. You can't add or delete things from it.
       

@{bg shine}WARNING@{bg back} : You use this program at your own risk. There is no warranty. The
entire risk as to the quality and performance of the software is with you. The
author is not responsible in any problem that can occur.

Indexeur is Copyright Christophe NOWAK in 1996.
@{"MUI" link "MUI" 0} is Copyright Stefan Stuntz.
Interface made with MUI-Builder , Copyright Eric Totel.
ImageFX Copyright NOVA Design.
@endnode

@node "Introduction" "Introduction"
@next "Indexeur"
@prev "A Propos"
This program needs :
        - an Amiga (2.x+)
        - @{"MUI" link "MUI" 0} 2.x
        - ARexx
        - ImageFX 1.2+

A hard disk, memory and a powerfull processor for a confortable use (for
ImageFX) will be welcome. But does anybody want to make pictures index from
floppy disks ?

It was successfully tested on :
        - A1200 with 2 megs of chip memory.
        - A4030 with 2 megs of chip and 4 megs of fast memory.
        - A4040 with 2 megs of chip and 12 megs of fast memory.

Only tested on ImageFX 1.2 and 2.0.

It should work on any Amiga which can use @{"MUI" link "MUI" 0} Applications and ImageFX.
@endnode

@node "Indexeur" "Indexeur"
@next "Prefs"
@prev "Introduction"
The program :

  It will create index pictures from a selection of pictures. For this, you must
select one or more pictures, choose the index format (number of pictures and
resolution), rendering mode and save format. Once all this parameters selected,
the program will reduce the pictures size, create the index with names and size
of each picture, and some other stuffs.
  You can also add pictures to an old not full index.

Interface description:

   -----------------------------------------------------------------
        @{"Resolution" link "Rķsolution" 0}         @{"Dithering" link "Dither" 0}           @{"IndexĀSize" link "Taille" 0}
        < radio >          < cycle >           < cycle >
        O Low Res                                                
        O High Res         @{"Direction" link "Direction" 0}           X Size < slider >
        O Super High Res   < cycle >           Y Size < slider >
                                               Nb X    < slider >
        O NoLace           @{"Colors" link "Couleurs" 0}              Nb Y    < slider >
        O Lace             < cycle >
                                                                    
                                                                    
     @{"IndexĀName" link "NomIndex" 0} < string > < popasl>     @{"SourceĀPictures" link "Sources" 0} < popasl >
    @{"ĀNotĀcompletedĀindexĀname" link "IndexNT" 0} < string > < popasl >  @{"Start" link "Dķbut" 0} < slider >

                               @{"Start" link "Dķmarrer" 0}

   -----------------------------------------------------------------
@endnode

