@node "Couleurs" "Cycle Colors"
@{b}Colors@{ub} : 
        - Select the number of colors for index rendering.
          Warning : if you choose GIF Save Format, colors must be <= 256.
@endnode

@node "Dķbut" "Start"
@{b}Start@{ub} :
        - Select where the program will start to put the stamps on an 
          allready defined index picture. Position value is between 1 and
          index format number of pictures.
          If it is a self-defined index format, beware that start position
          is in picture (a message will tell you if any problem).
@endnode

@node "Direction" "Dither Direction"
@{b}Direction@{ub} :
        - You can select the dithering direction like in ImageFX.
@endnode

@node "Dither" "Dither"
@{b}Dithering@{ub} :
        - You can select the dithering for rendering.
          Used if colors selection is not '24 bits'.
@endnode

@node "Dķmarrer" "Start"
@{b}Start@{ub} :
        - Start the index creation (you must have an index name and at
          least one picture selected).
          During the creation, the main window is closed and a progress
          window is opened. All the actions are described in it.
          There is a "Stop" button for cancelling the work.
          If a problem happens in ImageFX, the creation is stopped and
          a message is prompted.
          Special : if save command doesn't work (GIF format for a 24 bits
          index, no more memory for rendering,etc.), the program will let
          you save the index in IFF 24 bits.
@endnode

@node "IndexNT" "IndexNT"
@{b}Not completed Index Name@{ub} :
        - You can add pictures to a not full index picture.
          You must select the start position for the first picture and
          take care that the index format selected is the same that the
          old one.
@endnode

@node "NomIndex" "NomIndex"
@{b}Index Name@{ub} :
        - You must select a base name for the index.
          Index names will be : <name>.1, <name>.2, etc... with a save 
          format extension (JPEG,TARGA,ILBM or GIF).
@endnode

@node "Rķsolution" "Rķsolution"
@{b}Resolution@{ub} :
        - You can select the horizontal and vertical resolution
          of the rendering (only used if colors < 24 bits).
@endnode

@node "Sources" "Sources"
@{b}Source Pictures@{ub} :
        - You must select the pictures for the index. 
          For now, pictures have to be in the same directory. 
          If needed, i will make a better file selector.
@endnode

@node "Taille" "Taille"
@{b}Index Size@{ub} :
        - Enables you to select the index picture size.
          There are predefined sizes but you can also create your personal
          index size.
          The index size gives the picture size, the number of pictures
          per line and the number of lines.
          ex : 640*512 : 5*4 pictures means a 640*512 picture with
          4 lines with 5 pictures per line, so 20 pictures on index.
          If personnal configuration is selected, you can access sliders
          which can control the index format.
          You can define :
                - X Size : maximal width for a stamp.
                - Y Size : maximal height for a stamp.
                - Nb X : number of pictures per line.
                - Nb Y : number of lines.
          Index size will be : (X Size * Nb X)*(Y Size * Nb Y)
          Ex : if I want a 1280*512 index with 40 stamps, 10 stamps per line 
          and 4 lines, I will select : X Size = 128, Y Size = 128, 
          Nb X = 10, Nb Y = 4.
          X Size et Y Size will not be the exact size because they include
          the border size, the font size and the place between stamps.
@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"
@{b}Install@{ub} :

        - You can use the given installation script.
          (Installer needed).

        - for a handmade installation :
                - Copy Indexeur and its icon in the desired directory.
                - Copy the catalog file to LOCALE:catalogs/"your language"
                  if you need it.

        You must have : MUI, RexxMast and ImageFX 1.2+
@endnode

@node "SaveFormat" "Format de Sauvegarde"
@{b}Save Format@{ub} :
        - You can choose the save format of an index.
          4 formats are defined : IFF, GIF, TARGA, JPEG
          You can choose compressed TARGA or not.
          You can control the JPEG quality.
          @{bg shine}WARNING@{bg back} : if you select GIF you must 
          choose a 2 to 256 colors rendering.
          It's also recommended to choose a 24 bits rendering for a JPEG
          save format.
@endnode

@node "DelStamps" "Delete Stamps"
@{b}Delete Stamps@{ub} :
        - If selected, the stamps created by ImageFX will be 
          deleted after use. Stamps take place on disk but if for a
          picture, a stamp is present, it will be used for creating the 
          index so you will gain some speed and time.
          Don't delete stamps if you feel that the computer might crash,
          so it will not recalculate the already processed pictures.
          @{bg shine}WARNING@{bg back} : stamps are calculated for a specific index size
          so if you are making an index with a new size, delete the stamps
          before.
          Stamps name are : <name of the picture>.ndx
@endnode

@node "JPEGQuality" "JPEG Compression Quality"
@{b}JPEG Quality@{ub} :
        - Set the JPEG Compression quality (used if JPEG Save Format).
@endnode

@node "CompTarga" "Compressed Targa"
@{b}Compressed TARGA@{ub} :
        - if selected, TARGA file will be compressed (only used if TARGA 
          save format is selected ).
@endnode

@node "SaveStamp" "Stamps Save Directory"
@{b}Stamp Place@{ub} :
        - You can choose where the stamps will be saved.
          2 possibility :
                1 - In the same drawer that the pictures.
                2 - In the selected drawer.
@endnode

@node "Border" "Border Color"
@{b}Rectangle Color@{ub} :
        - You can choose the rectangle color of the stamps sides.
@endnode

@node "FontColor" "Couleur Police de caractĶre"
@{b}Font Color@{ub} : 
        - You can choose the color of the font used for the name of
          the pictures.
@endnode

@node "BackColor" "Couleur Fond Ecran"
@{b}Background Color@{ub} :
        - You can Select the index background color.
@endnode

@node "FontSpec" "Font Name and Size"
@{b}Font Name and Size@{ub} :
        - You can choose the font used for writing the pictures name.
          In this version, take care of the font size and especially
          of the font width, try some fonts (when a font is selected, I
          know the heigt but not the width).
          Default font is Topaz/8.
@endnode

@node "Boutons" "Prefs Buttons"
@{b}Save@{ub} : (also present in the menu)
        - Save the preferences.

@{b}Use@{ub} :  (also present in the menu)
        - Use the preferences without saving them.

@{b}Load@{ub} : (also present in the menu)
        - Load the last saved preferences.

@{b}Cancel@{ub} : (also present in the menu)
        - Cancel the modifications and restore the last used preferences.
@endnode

